<TITLE> New law on abandoned property okayed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com)  The interim cabinet on Thursday approved in principle the draft of the Bangladesh Abandoned Property (Control, Management and Disposal) (Amendment) Ordinance 2008, said a government statement. The proposed amendment of the abandoned property law is aimed at better management and control of moveable property in case any court, tribunal or the Law Commission confiscates such property, the statement said. Presided over by chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed, the cabinet meeting also conditionally approved the certification of industrial units in the environmentally critical area of Bhawal national park in Gazipur. The advisory council will certify such industrial units as were set up before a government notice up to June 29 2006. Regarding the industrial units set up on wholly private land, government restriction can be relaxed as per Bangladesh Wildlife (Conservation) Act, after verifying existing land survey records of ownership of the land, the government statement sdaid. Advisers and the CA's special assistants attended Thursday's meeting. bd
